"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830251","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-01","<p>Prevalence estimates for Lipoedema vary, though suggest a minimum of 1 in 72,000 women are affected. Approaches to treatment that may be offered by local National Health Service services are usually non-surgical and may include:</p><p> </p><p>- compression therapy (bandages or garments that squeeze the affected limbs);</p><p>- exercise (usually low-impact exercises, such as swimming); and</p><p>- massage (techniques that help encourage the flow of fluid through the body).</p><p> </p><p>Liposuction may be also considered, however there is limited evidence for its efficacy in the treatment of the condition and it is not routinely available on the NHS.</p><p> </p><p>As there has been little research into lipoedema, there is some uncertainty about the best way to treat the condition. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has not assessed, and therefore not approved, any approaches for the management or treatment of lipoedema.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","124915 ; 124917","2018-02-01T11:46:09.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830251/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830251/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830251/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-24","Lipoedema","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the number of women suffering from Lipedema.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","124912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830252","Department for Education","false","2018-01-31","<p>The ‘Schools that work for everyone’ consultation document proposed that we replace the 50% admissions cap on faith free schools with a series of strengthened safeguards to promote inclusivity.</p><p>We greatly value the important role faith schools play in our education system and as such, we plan to respond to these proposals regarding the establishment of new faith free schools in due course.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-01-31T15:09:03.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830252/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830252/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/830252/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-24","Faith Schools: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans he has to remove the 50 per cent admissions cap on faith schools.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy  Wilson","124913"
