"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828686","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-29","<p>The Secretary of State visited the London Borough of Redbridge on 19 January to take part in political campaigning. The Ministry of Justice does not hold information on this visit, due to its political nature.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","124342","2018-01-29T17:12:02.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828686/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828686/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828686/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-23","Domestic Visits: Redbridge","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will outline the itinerary of his visit to the London Borough of Redbridge that took place on 19 January 2018.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","124340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828687","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-29","<p>Carillion hold a number of contracts with the Department’s Arm’s Length Bodies (ALBs), including Network Rail. This includes rail electrification programme contracts.</p><p> </p><p>However, the electrification works between Manchester and Stalybridge, and between Manchester and Preston, are being delivered by a range of contractors, not just Carillion, and Amey are the principal contractor for those works.</p><p> </p><p>Network Rail also confirmed on Friday 19 January that Carillion staff working on their projects are guaranteed to get paid until at least mid-April 2018.</p><p> </p><p>This ensures that work will continue as planned on Network Rail projects through to mid-April 2018, by which point Network Rail expects to have alternative arrangements in place as necessary.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-01-29T16:14:54.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828687/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828687/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828687/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-23","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what rail improvement contracts Carillion holds in (a) the North West and (b) Manchester.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","124341"
